1
00:00:05,004 --> 00:00:08,456
What we mean 
when we say ‘devotee’,

2
00:00:08,472 --> 00:00:13,339
because Śrīla Gurudev,
liked to quote

3
00:00:13,339 --> 00:00:16,899
one of Śrīla Guru Mahārāj’s
godbrothers, saying,

4
00:00:16,899 --> 00:00:23,549
“Whether someone is 1 per cent a devotee, 
5 per cent, 25 per cent,

5
00:00:23,549 --> 00:00:28,149
50 per cent, 75 per cent, 
99 per cent,

6
00:00:28,149 --> 00:00:34,444
100 per cent,
that has to be factored in.

7
00:00:34,491 --> 00:00:37,330
[Love Transcends Good and Bad]

8
00:00:38,068 --> 00:00:41,816
What Guru Mahārāj sometimes
referred to as taṭastha vicār—

9
00:00:41,816 --> 00:00:49,119
impartial analysis to determine
higher, lower; superior, inferior;

10
00:00:49,119 --> 00:00:54,688
desirable, undesirable;
favourable, unfavourable.

11
00:00:54,688 --> 00:00:58,170
You have to be careful.

12
00:00:58,586 --> 00:01:03,235
What is it that compels us
to engage in this analysis?

13
00:01:03,327 --> 00:01:06,849
Curiosity? Envy?

14
00:01:06,849 --> 00:01:08,996
In the beginning of the Bhāgavatam,

15
00:01:08,996 --> 00:01:15,176
dharmaḥ projjhita-kaitavo ’tra paramo
nirmatsarāṇāḿ satāḿ [SB: 1.1.2]:

16
00:01:15,562 --> 00:01:19,557
this paramahaṃsa-saṁhitā,
 

17
00:01:19,557 --> 00:01:23,229
the qualification to enter into 
an understanding of the Bhāgavatam;

18
00:01:23,229 --> 00:01:27,686
the qualification to enter into
an understanding of Kṛṣṇa conciousness;

19
00:01:27,686 --> 00:01:33,301
the qualification to understand
the devotees, nirmātsarya—

20
00:01:33,301 --> 00:01:38,041
to not be envious of them.
What does that mean?

21
00:01:38,041 --> 00:01:44,200
I mean it’s a negative prescription
or prohibition,

22
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:48,346
but it has a positive implication.

23
00:01:48,346 --> 00:01:51,529
Negative, not to be envious.
What is envy?

24
00:01:51,529 --> 00:01:53,561
Defined in this context,

25
00:01:53,561 --> 00:02:03,168
is to not allow someone to be seen
in their rightful position.

26
00:02:03,321 --> 00:02:05,891
To not recognise that,

27
00:02:05,907 --> 00:02:09,324
and to be more specific,
to not recognise devotion,

28
00:02:09,324 --> 00:02:13,988
to not recognise
devotional tendency.

29
00:02:14,296 --> 00:02:18,274
Nehābhikrama-nāśo ’sti
pratyavāyo na vidyate

30
00:02:18,274 --> 00:02:22,491
sv-alpam apy asya dharmasya
trāyate mahato bhayāt [Bg: 2.40]

31
00:02:22,491 --> 00:02:31,148
A little bit of this is extraordinary
and eternally beneficial.

32
00:02:31,148 --> 00:02:41,450
So these other aspects of a person
in terms of flaws, perceived defects,

33
00:02:41,450 --> 00:02:45,245
whether they be character flaws
or improper behaviour etc.

34
00:02:45,245 --> 00:02:49,496
they’re not eternal characteristics.

35
00:02:49,496 --> 00:02:53,040
They might temporarily show something
and vanish,

36
00:02:53,040 --> 00:03:02,379
whereas the devotional tendency is 
of a lasting, permanent, eternal nature.

37
00:03:02,755 --> 00:03:10,692
Śrīla Gurudev, when he was giving
some of his final words,

38
00:03:10,692 --> 00:03:18,357
he said that everyone has
some fault, something;

39
00:03:18,358 --> 00:03:24,324
and whether it is big or small,
that is not the question.

40
00:03:24,324 --> 00:03:30,034
And he said that with the same cadence
of the famous Shakespearean

41
00:03:30,034 --> 00:03:33,072
“To be or not to be, 
that is the question.”

42
00:03:33,072 --> 00:03:38,703
So Gurudev said,
“Big or small, that is not the question.”

43
00:03:38,703 --> 00:03:45,160
He said, “But what must be recognised
is their devotional tendency,

44
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:47,498
serving tendency”,
and he said,

45
00:03:47,498 --> 00:03:51,507
“that must be recognised
and respected.”

46
00:03:51,507 --> 00:03:59,328
So that is the vision
of the devotees.

47
00:03:59,482 --> 00:04:06,180
Guru Mahārāj says our only hope
of connecting with the upper world,

48
00:04:06,180 --> 00:04:10,119
what to speak of the highest aspect 
of the upper world, Goloka Vṛndāvan—

49
00:04:10,119 --> 00:04:12,780
what is it known as? 
—The land of love.

50
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:19,663
Love conceals all deficiencies.

51
00:04:20,231 --> 00:04:29,430
And if we recognised that
despite someone’s apparent flaws,

52
00:04:29,430 --> 00:04:35,936
that they do have some serving tendency,
spirit of devotion, dedication,

53
00:04:35,936 --> 00:04:39,289
then it’ll be better for us to think

54
00:04:39,289 --> 00:04:42,210
if I could get
a little bit of that from them,

55
00:04:42,210 --> 00:04:44,472
what they’ve got, 
the good thing they’ve got,

56
00:04:44,472 --> 00:04:46,928
my position will improve.

57
00:04:46,928 --> 00:04:49,028
So let me think of them
in such a way
 

58
00:04:49,028 --> 00:04:50,615
and deal with them 
in such a way,

59
00:04:50,615 --> 00:04:54,764
to appreciate
their dedicating tendency,

60
00:04:54,764 --> 00:05:00,568
and maybe some grace
will come to me from that.

